message:
@Chris_Huntley, If I had my druthers, I'd actually like to hear you get *more* theoretical, not less. (Although the above post was helpful.)

To me, knowing that something can be explored temporally or spacially is just scratching the surface. The program gives us the practical way to do that -- laying out the signposts, etc. -- but I'd love to know how you think it affects meaning.

I've done enough storyweaving and editing to know that a slap followed by a scream is not the same as a scream followed by a slap. But, to know how Fate followed by Destiny is different from Destiny followed by Fate... that's beyond me right now.
